    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Ultimate Equipment pg. 43</em>, <em>Ultimate Combat pg. 137</em></p>\n<h3 class=\"framing\"><img style=\"margin: 3px 3px 0px 3px;\" title=\"No character may purchase a firearm unless she possesses the Gunsmithing feat and firearms are never considered Always Available\" src=\"https://www.aonprd.com/images/PathfinderSocietySymbolN.gif\" />Statistics</h3>\n<p><strong>Cost</strong> 1,600 gp <strong>Weight</strong> 6 lbs.</p>\n<p><strong>Damage</strong> 1d6 (small), 1d8 (medium); <strong>Critical</strong> x4; <strong>Range</strong> 30 ft.; <strong>Type</strong> B and P; <strong>Special</strong> -</p>\n<p><strong>Misfire</strong> 1-2 (5 ft.); <strong>Capacity</strong> 1</p>\n<p><strong>Category</strong> Two-Handed; <strong>Proficiency</strong> Exotic</p>\n<h3 class=\"framing\">Description</h3>\n<p>This short musket features an axe blade at the end of its barrel. It can be used as both a musket and a battleaxe. It is considered a double weapon for the purposes of creating masterwork or magical versions of this weapon.</p>\n<p>If this firearm gains the broken condition, both the firearm component and the axe are considered broken. An axe musket uses either a bullet and a single dose of black powder or an alchemical cartridge as ammunition.</p>\n<p><strong>This is an early firearm.</strong></p>"
